shape: sequence_diagram
vars: {
  d2-config: {
    # layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
classes: @"../classes/sequence"
user: {shape: person; class: obj_client}
app_R: {label: app.R; class: obj_service}
server: {label: server.R; class: obj_server}
chess_py: {label: python-chess (reticulate); class: obj_service}
connector: {label: connector API; class: obj_server}
shiny: {class: obj_server}

app_R.note1: |md
  ```
  source utilities (fen_map, find_index_of_rank, …)
  source ui.R and server.R
  read API_URL from env (default http://localhost:8000)
  ```
|
app_R -> shiny: shinyApp(ui, server) on port 3838

server.note1: |md
  ```
  import chess via reticulate
  init reactive values:
  asciiBoard, helperVisual, links, fenDescription, moveHistory
  ```
|

user -> server: select preset FEN or submit FEN {class: edge_request}
server -> chess_py: board.set_fen(fen) {class: edge_write}
server -> connector: "GET /links?fen_string=<FEN>" {class: edge_request}
server.note2: |md
  ```
  updateChessDependencies():
  render ASCII board
  call fenMap() for visualization
  generate FEN description (YAML)
  update move history
  ```
|

user -> server: submit move {class: edge_request}
server -> chess_py: board.push_san(move) {class: edge_write}
server -> connector: "GET /links?fen_string=<updated FEN>" {class: edge_request}

user -> server: undo {class: edge_request}
server -> chess_py: board.pop() {class: edge_write}
